commit.message:
Drop shell and python implementations

The C implementation works everywhere and has no dependencies aside from
standard library and system header files. This cannot be said of the other
two. Remove them to declutter the repository.

Default to C implementation

Does not rely on external utilities and now works on Linux and FreeBSD.

commit.message:
wayland-logout.c: port to FreeBSD

Keep it separately to make the main code easy to read.

wayland-logout.sh: try sockstat on BSDs

lsof is slow on FreeBSD and not supported on DragonFly.

Use SIGTERM instead of SIGINT

This is consistent with the default kill signal and works even if the compositor has been backgrounded.
